verbose_text: A small subset of histone genes had reduced levels of 22G-RNAs in henn-1 mutants, suggesting that henn-1-dependent 22G-RNAs may have a role in regulating histones, although it is possible that altered cell physiology in henn-1 mutants indirectly impacts histone levels (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY; XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
evidence: histone genes had reduced levels of 22G-RNAs in henn-1 mutants
